+  summaryLines.push(`The full multivariable feature model explained R-squared ${fmt(fullFit.r2)} of pfs_months variation. Several hypotheses were supported after adjustment, especially feature_041, feature_050, feature_025, feature_015, feature_036, and the top binary features. The deliberate negative-control style hypothesis in iteration 25 for ${nullFeatures.name} was not supported, with small nonsignificant unadjusted and adjusted effects.`);
+  summaryLines.push("");
+  summaryLines.push("Because feature names are opaque, these results should be interpreted as treatment/biomarker/clinical-feature associations rather than causal effects. The strongest conclusion is that pfs_months in this cohort is heterogeneous: baseline-like variables, categorical clinical strata, multiple binary markers, and specific interactions each contribute measurable differences in progression-free survival.");
+
